) in Burke's Dormant, Abeyant, Forfeited and Extinct Peerages, pg. 271","description":"Herbert (Herbertus Camerarius) in Burke's Dormant, Abeyant, Forfeited and Extinct Peerages, pg. 271. It is noted that this record skips the son of Herbertus Camerarius, Henry FitzHerbert, and goes to Herbert's grandson (called his son), also named Herbert (Herbert FitzHenry or Herbert FitzHerbert I).","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1060","birthPlace":{"address":"Vermandois, Aisne, Picardy, France","geo":{"latitude":49.5,"longitude":3.5,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1119","deathPlace":{"address":"Winchester, Hampshire, England","geo":{"latitude":51.06906,"longitude":-1.32045,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"sourceList":[{"title":"Legacy NFS Source: Herbert Fitzherbert - Church record: birth: about 1035; England, United Kingdom","sourceType":"LEGACY","sourceUri":"MSW1-LWW"},{"title":"Herbert FitzHenry","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/enguntdk.htm#HerbertChamberlain","sourceUri":"Q3Y9-J9C"},{"title":"Herbert the Chamberlain (Herbertus Camerarius), in A Genealogical and Heraldic History of the Landed Gentry of Great Britain and Ireland, Vol. 1, pg. 613 [but missing the generation of Henry the Treasurer). ","sourceType":"USER_UPLOADED","sourceLink":"http://familysearch.org/patron/source/photoId/165545565","sourceUri":"QSSS-5FD"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"3","year":"1060","date":"Abt 1060","place":"Vermandois, Aisne, Picardy, France"},{"name":"Occupation","sources":"0","year":"1066","date":"1066","age":"6"},{"name":"Occupation","sources":"0","year":"1066","date":"1066","age":"6"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1087","date":"before 1087","place":"Wales","type":"Spousal","age":"26","id":"L8YY-B7R"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1087","date":"about 1087","place":"Wales","age":"27","id":"G8TV-XDQ"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1088","date":"1088","place